Lets consider a 2-D matrix table for this question where -
 - Rows equal size of the childhood string. Let&#39;s call this `n`.
 - Cols equal total number of alphabet blocks. (4, 6, 5 in examples 1, 2 and 3). Lets call this `m`. They basically are the number of strings to be checked against.

In the `n x m` 2-D boolean matrix, if the `ith` character of the string is present in the `jth` block, we mark `table[i][j] = true;` Else it is marked as false. I&#39;ve used the diagram below for the first example.

```
_ | UPZRHR | INOYLC | KXDHNQ | BAGMZI
D | false  | false  | true   | false
O | false  | true   | false  | false
G | false  | false  | false  | true
``` 
Now, a block can satisfy for all the letters of the childhood string. But for each and every character in the childhood string, we want a distinct alphabet block.

How do we go about this ?
Well, for every `table[i][j] = true`, we store `i` and `j` in 2 separate sets, `i` in the row set and `j` in the column set.

The size of the row-set should be exactly equal to the size of the childhood string. This means that every character in the childhood string is found in one of the alphabet blocks. &lt;br&gt;
The size of the column-set should be greater than or equal to the size of the childhood string. This means that we are able to make the string from distinct alphabet block.

If the above condition isn&#39;t satisfied we cannot make our childhood string.

Below is the function in c++. I&#39;ve modified the way I take my input but the logic remains the same.

```
void solve() {
    string str; cin &gt;&gt; str; // chilhood string
    
    int n; cin &gt;&gt; n;
    
    vector&lt;string&gt; v(n);   // other strings
    for(string&amp; s: v) cin &gt;&gt; s;
    
    // table
    vector&lt;vector&lt;bool&gt;&gt; dp(str.size(), vector&lt;bool&gt;(n, false));
    for(int i=0; i&lt;str.size(); i++) {
        for(int j=0; j&lt;n; j++) {
            dp[i][j] = (v[j].find(str[i]) != string::npos) ? true: false;
        }
    }
    
    unordered_set&lt;int&gt; row, col;
    for(int i=0; i&lt;str.size(); i++) {
        for(int j=0; j&lt;n; j++) {
            if(dp[i][j] == true) {
                row.insert(i);
                col.insert(j);
            }
        }
    }

    cout &lt;&lt; ((row.size() == str.size() &amp;&amp; col.size() &gt;= str.size()) ? &quot;true&quot;: &quot;false&quot;) &lt;&lt; &#39;\n&#39;;
}
```

