Like most methods in `File`, `listFiles()` doesn&#39;t throw an exception if it can&#39;t read the files, but instead returns `null`. That&#39;s documented, and that&#39;s what&#39;s happening here.

Try the following to see _why_ you can&#39;t read the contents:
```java
try (DirectoryStream&lt;Path&gt; directoryStream = Files.newDirectoryStream(my_folder.toPath())) {
    for (Path myFile : directoryStream) {
        System.out.println(myFile);
    }
}
```
That will most likely throw an `IOException` that tells you what went wrong.

